---
// /bible-in/brazil — Portuguese, majority-Christian. Faith-framing variant =
// "nominal-Christian": Brazil is ~84% Christian, but the invitation is to MEET
// the Father in the Bible they already have, not to bring a first Bible. Data
// cited in sources/painsSources. Mirrors the India template. Photos: Wikimedia.
import CountryBible from '../../components/CountryBible.astro';

const verses = [
	{
		ref: 'Romans 8:15',
		slug: 'romans',
		ch: 8,
		text: 'For you did not receive a spirit of slavery to fall back into fear, but you received the Spirit of adoption as sons, by whom we cry, “Abba! Father!”',
	},
	{
		ref: 'John 3:16',
		slug: 'john',
		ch: 3,
		text: 'For our Father so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life.',
	},
	{
		ref: 'Luke 15:20',
		slug: 'luke',
		ch: 15,
		text: 'And he arose and came to his father. But while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and felt compassion, and ran and embraced him and kissed him.',
	},
];

const stats = [
	{ label: 'People', value: '217 million' },
	{ label: 'Language', value: 'Portuguese' },
	{ label: 'Christians', value: '~150 million' },
	{ label: 'Bible market', value: '#1 in the world' },
];

const faqs = [
	{
		question: 'Can I read the Bible online free in Brazil?',
		answer:
			"Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read online with audio — no account, no purchase, no app. It is currently in English, which many Brazilians read; a Brazilian Portuguese edition is among our highest translation priorities, so the whole nation can read it in its own tongue.",
	},
	{
		question: "Is the Father's Heart Bible available in Portuguese?",
		answer:
			'Not yet — but Portuguese, spoken by some 257 million people across Brazil and Lusophone Africa, is at the very top of our translation roadmap. Brazil is the largest Bible market in the world, and giving it a Bible that reveals God as Father in Portuguese is a central goal.',
	},
	{
		question: 'I already have a Bible — why another translation?',
		answer:
			"Brazil is rich in Bibles and churches, yet many people relate to God as a distant authority, an obligation, or a means to prosperity. The Father's Heart Bible™ renders God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him that way — turning a familiar book into a Father's letter to a son or daughter you may never have known you were.",
	},
	{
		question: 'Is there an audio Bible I can listen to?',
		answer:
			"Yes. Every chapter of the Father's Heart Bible™ comes with free audio, so you can listen on any phone. Globally, audio Scripture is surging, with more than 1.3 billion audio-Bible listens recorded in a single year.",
	},
];
---

<CountryBible
	slug="brazil"
	country="Brazil"
	flag="🇧🇷"
	flagImg="/flags/br.svg"
	countryWikipedia="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil"
	lastUpdated="June 2026"
	lastUpdatedIso="2026-06-13"
	colorPrimary="#009C3B"
	colorSecondary="#FFCC29"
	colorAccent="#002776"
	tintWarm="#FFF7DC"
	tintCool="#E8F5EC"
	tintBlue="#E6ECF5"
	title="The Bible in Brazil — Read Free Online with Audio | Father's Heart Bible™"
	description="Read the Bible free online in Brazil, with audio. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as Father — in the largest Bible nation on earth. English now, Portuguese a top priority."
	h1="The Bible in Brazil"
	heroSubhead="In the largest Bible nation on earth — a fresh translation that lets you meet God not as a distant religion, but as a Father. Free online, with audio."
	heroBase="https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/5f3eac722a31c44eaa305a80dbf004c27a222df7-4680x3744.jpg"
	heroAlt="The Christ the Redeemer statue overlooking Rio de Janeiro, Brazil"
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style=\"color: var(--color-ink);\">Yes &mdash; you can read the Bible free online in Brazil right now.</strong> The <a href=\"https://fathersheartbible.com/read\" style=\"color: var(--color-brand);\" class=\"hover:underline\">Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade;</a> is free to read and <em>hear</em> on any phone, with no app and no account. Brazil is the most Bible-saturated nation on earth &mdash; and yet, for all its churches, the Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; offers something many have never met: God revealed as a <em>Father</em>, not a distant authority to appease. It is available in English today, and a Brazilian Portuguese edition is one of our highest priorities.`}
	keyTakeaway="Brazil has more Bibles than almost anywhere — but the Father's Heart Bible™ invites you to finally meet the Father inside the book you already know."
	glanceIntroHtml={`Brazil is a continent of a country &mdash; the largest in Latin America, the most populous Catholic nation on earth, and home to a vast and fast-growing evangelical church. It is a land of staggering natural beauty and equally staggering contrasts.`}
	stats={stats}
	knownForHeading="What Brazil is known for"
	knownForIntroHtml={`Few nations are loved by the world the way Brazil is &mdash; for its warmth, its rhythm, and its sheer natural abundance.`}
	knownFor={[
		{ label: 'Christ over the city', text: 'The Christ the Redeemer statue above Rio is one of the New Seven Wonders of the World — arms open over a nation.' },
		{ label: 'The lungs of the planet', text: 'The Amazon, the world’s largest rainforest, holds about 10% of all known species on earth.' },
		{ label: 'The beautiful game', text: 'Brazil has won the FIFA World Cup a record five times — football here is less a sport than a national language.' },
		{ label: 'Iguazu and wild wonders', text: 'From the thundering Iguazu Falls to the Pantanal wetlands, Brazil holds some of the planet’s greatest natural spectacles.' },
		{ label: 'A culture of music and joy', text: 'Samba, bossa nova, and Carnival gave the world a vocabulary for celebration.' },
		{ label: 'The largest Bible nation', text: 'Brazil receives and reads more Bibles than any country on earth — Scripture is woven into daily life.' },
	]}
	gallery={[
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/d877fb2ca88c10ff8ca53685f79a307553b4f725-4200x2800.jpg', alt: 'Iguazu Falls on the Brazilian side' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/29209b950d564b84a4e54dc13cf6c90629eaa11c-3709x2473.jpg', alt: 'Sugarloaf Mountain and the bay of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e6d398b8368cfd733ec582b8b84baa22490cd4f6-6736x4493.jpg', alt: 'Copacabana beach in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/1a4e1410dc738d2551580a64e85198ab202d3e09-4608x3456.jpg', alt: 'The colorful colonial Pelourinho district in Salvador, Brazil' },
	]}
	galleryCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a>.`}
	galleryBottom={[
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/226e0e67063650af99139a12885eb18c5d5fa693-3450x2118.jpg', alt: 'Aerial view of the Amazon rainforest, Brazil' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/5d71aa65eca7e94a20db7a57ee35d6d9c201440b-9000x6000.jpg', alt: 'The historic colonial town of Ouro Preto, Brazil' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/fc30bbd89d4c5e7aca5eec923745d5b35cba6b8b-5184x3456.jpg', alt: 'The Pantanal wetlands of Brazil' },
		{ src: 'https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/a922b13d6234879280deb56b039050c97868c5b6-3264x2176.jpg', alt: 'People playing beach football on a Brazilian beach' },
	]}
	galleryBottomCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a>.`}
	faithHeading="Faith and the Bible in Brazil"
	faithBodyHtml={`<p>No nation reads more of the Bible than Brazil. It is the most populous Catholic country on earth &mdash; about <strong>100 million Catholics</strong> &mdash; and home to the second-largest Protestant population in the Western world, with <strong>47 million evangelicals</strong> and growing fast. All told, roughly <strong>84% of Brazilians are Christian</strong>.</p><p>Brazil is also the <strong>largest Bible market in the world</strong> &mdash; more Bibles are printed, sold, and distributed here than anywhere else. Scripture saturates the culture, from favela storefront churches to vast stadium services.</p><p>And yet, for all that abundance, many Brazilians carry a quiet ache: God is known <em>about</em> &mdash; as a rule-giver, a tradition, or a means to prosperity &mdash; more than He is known <em>as Father</em>. The need in Brazil is not a first Bible. It is to meet, inside the book they already revere, the Father who has loved them all along.</p>`}
	sources={[
		{ label: 'Brazil 2022 Census — religion (Christianity Today)', url: 'https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/06/religion-brazil-census-2022/' },
		{ label: 'Bible distribution (Brazil #1)', url: 'https://www.christiantoday.com/news/digital-bible-distribution-outstrips-print-worldwide-for-the-first-time' },
	]}
	painsHeading="What pains Brazil"
	painsIntroHtml={`Behind the beaches and the joy, Brazilian families carry heavy and unequal burdens &mdash; and it is into these exact wounds that the Father&rsquo;s heart speaks.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: '36,427', label: 'lives lost to homicide in 2024 — among the highest totals on earth' },
		{ value: '0.504', label: 'Gini index — one of the most unequal societies in the world' },
		{ value: '80%', label: 'of families carry debt — a record high' },
		{ value: '71%', label: 'of those in poverty are Black or mixed-race, though they are 57% of the population' },
		{ value: '7.4 million', label: 'people still live in extreme poverty' },
		{ value: '#1', label: 'in the Americas for total homicides — concentrated in poor communities' },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>The violence falls hardest on the young, the poor, and the Black &mdash; a generation of sons and daughters lost in the favelas and the urban margins. Inequality runs so deep that two Brazils live side by side, and household debt has reached record levels. Many homes are marked by absent fathers, and the wound of fatherlessness runs through it all.</p><p>These are not statistics to a Father. They are children He longs to gather. Brazil does not need more religion &mdash; it needs to know it is loved by a Father who runs to meet His children.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: 'Brazil homicide data 2024 (Statista)', url: 'https://www.statista.com/statistics/867725/homicide-rate-brazil/' },
		{ label: 'Poverty & inequality 2024 (IBGE / Agência Brasil)', url: 'https://agenciabrasil.ebc.com.br/en/economia/noticia/2025-12/over-86-million-escape-poverty-brazil-hits-best-level-2012' },
	]}
	faithsHeading="What “our Father” offers Brazil"
	faithsIntroHtml={`Brazil already believes. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; does not bring a new religion &mdash; it answers the longing underneath the religion Brazil already has: to be a beloved child, not a distant subject. For the first time in a fresh translation, Scripture reveals God not as a force to appease, but as a <em>Father</em> who runs to meet His children.`}
	faithsBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'For the one who has a Bible but not a Father', bodyHtml: `You have heard of God your whole life. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; lets you finally meet Him &mdash; <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/luke/15" style="color: var(--color-gold);" class="hover:underline">the Father who runs to the returning child</a>, not a rule-keeper to satisfy.` },
		{ heading: 'For the fatherless', bodyHtml: `In a land where so many homes are missing a father, Scripture offers <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/romans/8" style="color: var(--color-gold);" class="hover:underline">the Spirit of adoption</a> &mdash; a Father who calls you His own son, His own daughter, forever.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one crushed by inequality', bodyHtml: `Across the divide between the two Brazils, the Father calls every person &mdash; favela or penthouse &mdash; equally beloved. Belonging here is not bought; it is given.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one tired of earning God&rsquo;s favor', bodyHtml: `To everyone worn out by religion that demands and prosperity gospels that disappoint, the Father offers a love that comes first and keeps no ledger of wrongs.` },
	]}
	whyHeading="Why the Father's Heart Bible for Brazil"
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'God revealed as Father, not religion', bodyHtml: `In the most Bible-rich nation on earth, the Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; offers what familiarity can dull: God revealed as <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture reveals Him that way &mdash; from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1:1</a> onward.` },
		{ heading: 'Free, with audio, on any phone', bodyHtml: `No purchase, no app, no sign-up. The whole Bible is free to <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">read online</a> with audio on every chapter &mdash; built for a basic smartphone.` },
		{ heading: 'A Portuguese edition is coming', bodyHtml: `English is available today, and Portuguese &mdash; 257 million speakers across Brazil and Lusophone Africa &mdash; sits at the very top of our <a href="/bible-in/brazil/#translation-opportunity" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">translation roadmap</a>.` },
	]}
	resourcesHeading="Learn more about Brazil"
	resourcesIntroHtml={`Trusted sources for the facts on this page &mdash; and for going deeper into Brazil&rsquo;s people, faith, and story.`}
	resources={[
		{ label: 'Brazil — Wikipedia', url: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil' },
		{ label: 'Religion in Brazil — Wikipedia', url: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religion_in_Brazil' },
		{ label: 'Brazil 2022 Census on religion — Christianity Today', url: 'https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/06/religion-brazil-census-2022/' },
		{ label: 'Brazil — Encyclopaedia Britannica', url: 'https://www.britannica.com/place/Brazil' },
		{ label: 'Brazil — Joshua Project (people groups)', url: 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/BR' },
	]}
	opportunityHeading="The translation opportunity in Brazil"
	opportunityIntroHtml={`Brazil reads the Bible like no other nation &mdash; but to read it in the Father&rsquo;s own voice, in their own Portuguese, is a door still waiting to open for 200 million people.`}
